                <h5>Lab-Grown Diamonds Are Identical to Natural Diamonds</h5>
                <p>Lab-grown diamonds, although man-made, are physically and chemically identical to natural diamonds that are mined. Nobody can tell the two apart and a highly specialised piece of equipment is used to sort the lab-created diamonds from the natural ones. Since both the composition and the structure of engineered diamonds are the same as natural ones,<strong>America’s Federal Trade Commission (FTC) amended its Jewelry Guide to remove the word ‘natural’ from the definition of a diamond.</strong>This means that a diamond is a diamond, regardless of whether it comes out of the ground or was made in a laboratory.</p>
                <h5>Lab-Grown Diamonds – A Great Choice!</h5>
                <p>If lab-grown diamonds and natural diamonds are exactly the same – is one better than the other? Absolutely! Lab-made diamonds have a slight edge over natural diamonds. Lab-grown stones do not require extensive mining, which means that obtaining a diamond is no longer an expensive and long-drawn process. This directly translates into more <strong>affordable diamonds</strong> for you. </p>
                <p>For years we’ve been told that only mined diamonds that are rare are real, but that is no longer the case. Lab-grown diamonds are just as real as natural ones – but they are heavy on style while being lighter on your pocket!</p>
